==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sibyl
<hw>Sib"yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sibylla</ets>,
Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Class. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A
woman supposed to be endowed with a spirit of prophecy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The number of the sibyls is variously stated by
different authors; but the opinion of Varro, that there were ten, is
generally adopted. They dwelt in various parts of Persia, Greece, and
Italy.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A female fortune teller; a pythoness; a
prophetess.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An old highland <xex>sibyl</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sibylist</ent>⟦br⟧
